### Context

A while ago we proposed an alternative way to send emails in Symfony apps. See https://github.com/symfony/symfony/issues/15060  At that time, @stof cleverly spotted several problems related to Twig ... but the Twig 1.28 version introduced some features that probably will solve all of our problems.

### Proposal

I propose to add a `renderAndSend()` method as an alternative to `send()`. This pull request is a **super early proof of concept draft**. This is just to see if this idea is doable or stupid.

### Examples

For simple emails where everything is static, you can do this:

```php
$this->get('mailer')->renderAndSend('emails/registration.twig');
```

And the template:

```twig
{# app/Resources/views/emails/registration.twig #}
{% block to 'user@example.com' %}
{% block from 'donotreply@example.com' %}
{% block subject %}Welcome to ACME{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    ...
    <div> ... </div>
    ...
{% endblock %}
```

If the template needs parameters, pass them as an array in the optional second argument:

```php
$this->get('mailer')->renderAndSend('emails/registration.twig', array(
    'name' => $name
));
```

This second argument also allows to define the value of some email message paramenters: `to`, `from`, `cc`, `bcc`, `subject`, `body` and `body_txt`:

```php
$this->get('mailer')->renderAndSend('emails/registration.twig', array(
    'from' => 'send@example.com',
    'to' => 'recipient@example.com',
    'subject' => 'Hello Email',
    'name' => $name,
));
```

