The issue is, that saveMessage() and restoreMessage() in the Message class do not restore/save the encoding. So the signer will change that and it is not restored.

Example:

``` php
<?php 
require_once 'swiftmailer/lib/swift_required.php';
$dir = 'swiftmailer/tests/_samples/';
$message = Swift_SignedMessage::newInstance('Wonderful Subject')
  ->setFrom(array('john@doe.com' => 'John Doe'))
  ->setTo(array('receiver@domain.org', 'other@domain.org' => 'A name'))
  ->setBody('Here is the message itself');

$signer = new Swift_Signers_SMimeSigner();
$signer->setSignCertificate($dir.'smime/sign.crt', $dir.'smime/sign.key');
$message->attachSigner($signer);
assert($message->toString() == $message->toString());
?>
```

