I allow clients to create their own templates and I use those when composing the e-mail. When the e-mail client would try to display the HTML version of the e-mail it would have the full message, and then a partial piece of the next message.

After a bit of searching I realized that the apostrophe in the template was not a true apostrophe. It was Microsoft Word's version of the apostrophe. My client had typed up their template in Word and copy pasted it over.

I ended up just adding a find/replace before passing my message to addPart and that was the quick fix.

```
$html = preg_replace('~“|”~', '"', $html);
